Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Halve, core, and thinly slice @green bell pepper{1}(halved, cored and sliced into strips).

Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. (Save potatoes for another use.)

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, and half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}(divided). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Swap in broccoli for potatoes; roast 15-20 minutes.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and bell pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Transfer to a plate.

While veggies cook, in a second #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine remaining garlic powder and @butter{2%tablespoon}; microwave until butter is just softened, ~{10-15%seconds}. Stir to combine and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}; set aside.

Slice @demi-baguette{2} lengthwise, stopping before you get all the way through; spread garlic butter onto cut sides. Place cut sides up on a second #baking sheet{}.

Toast on middle rack until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

While garlic buns toast, pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add chicken and @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}; cook, stirring, until chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and @water{2%tablespoon}(divided). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Return veggies to pan; stir to combine.

Spread cut sides of bottom buns with half the garlic sauce. Top with chicken and veggie mixture, then sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{½%cup}. Return to middle rack until cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Divide sandwiches and potatoes between plates. Serve with remaining garlic sauce on the side for dipping.